Package Classes

Class Event

java.lang.Object
Classes.Event
public class Event extends Object
Event The Event class represents an event organized within the application. It stores various attributes related to the event, such as dates, maximum participants, geolocation settings, and references to associated resources.

      public Event(String organizerID, String eventTitle, Date regOpenDate, Date regDeadlineDate, Date eventStartDate, Integer maxWinners, Integer maxEntrants, String eventDetails, String eventPictureURL, boolean enableGeolocation, String listReference, String LocationReference, String QRCode)
      Complete Event Constructor
      Parameters:
      organizerID - Unique ID of the event organizer
      eventTitle - Title of the event
      regOpenDate - Date when registration opens
      regDeadlineDate - Date when registration closes
      eventStartDate - Date when the event starts
      maxWinners - Maximum number of winners for the event
      maxEntrants - Maximum number of participants allowed
      eventDetails - Description and details of the event
      eventPictureURL - URL for the event's image
      enableGeolocation - Indicates if geolocation is enabled for the event
      listReference - Reference ID of the associated event list document
      LocationReference - Reference ID of the associated location document
      QRCode - QR code for event identification
